00:00:09:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:09:000000.Dialogue: Please. We're facing a far more serious problem than stray arachnids.

00:00:14:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:14:210000.Dialogue: Not bad? It's horrible. You hear stories about this things, but you never think it'll happen to you.

00:00:20:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:20:200000.Dialogue: So they steamed your dumplings. Get over it.

00:00:36:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:36:120000.Dialogue: Not with a thousand condoms, Howard.

00:00:45:020000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:45:020000.Dialogue: Okay, new topic, please. Did you hear the people upstairs in 5A are moving out?

00:00:58:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:58:180000.Dialogue: Why would you just say something like that?

00:01:04:150000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:04:150000.Dialogue: - How else was I supposed to say it?

00:01:11:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:11:100000.Dialogue: You let the bag sit in the water a while.

00:01:18:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:18:030000.Dialogue: - I'm sure it's going to be fine.

00:01:25:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:25:140000.Dialogue: Honey, did you even know the people that are moving out?

00:01:28:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:28:090000.Dialogue: I never met them. That's what made them perfect.

00:01:32:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:32:070000.Dialogue: There were no awkward hellos in the halls. There's no clickety-clacking of high heel shoes on hardwood floors. They may as well have been a family of cats just jumping around from drape to drape.

00:01:43:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:43:060000.Dialogue: Without that annoying ammonia urine smell.

00:01:47:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:47:210000.Dialogue: I'm sure the new people will be just as quiet.

00:01:50:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:50:070000.Dialogue: You can't know that. How can you possibly know that?

00:01:53:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:53:110000.Dialogue: You're right, I can't. You know what? Anyone could rent that apartment now: an opera singer, the cast of Stomp...

00:02:02:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:02:040000.Dialogue: Yeah, a tap-dancing pirate with a wooden leg.

00:02:06:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:06:190000.Dialogue: Why are you making it worse?

00:02:08:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:02:08:080000.Dialogue: I tried making it better. He wouldn't go for it.

00:02:12:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:12:130000.Dialogue: You're right! That's a great idea.

00:02:16:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:16:110000.Dialogue: I can finally get away from my mother and we can all spend some more time together. If you catch my drift.

00:02:51:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:51:210000.Dialogue: Hold on. You honestly expect me to believe that social protocol dictates we break our backs helping Wolowitz move, and then he only need buy us a pizza?

00:03:02:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:02:040000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, that really is how it works.

00:03:08:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:08:070000.Dialogue: You tell me the truth, what do we get?

00:03:13:090000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:13:090000.Dialogue: You get to choose between a mountain bike or a PS3.

00:03:21:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:21:130000.Dialogue: Who would pick a mountain bike?

00:03:27:030000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:27:030000.Dialogue: We'll still see each other. I'll come over every night and have dinner with you.

00:03:34:100000.Speaker: Howard’s Mother
00:03:34:100000.Dialogue: What am I running here, a fancy restaurant?

00:03:38:180000.Speaker: Howard’s Mother
00:03:38:180000.Dialogue: Does this look like Olive Garden?!

00:03:43:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:43:020000.Dialogue: Okay, I get it, you're angry. You don't want to see your little bird leave the nest.

00:03:55:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:55:020000.Dialogue: Fine, I'll stay! Ya happy, crazy lady? I sure as hell hope so, because you're ruining my life!

00:04:03:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:03:090000.Dialogue: Hey, Penny? Good news, you can take your head out of the oven.

00:04:08:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:08:170000.Dialogue: I guess I won't be needing this.

00:05:15:050000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:05:26:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:26:160000.Dialogue: On a scale of one to ten, how light of foot would you describe yourself, with one being not cat-like at all, and ten being freakishly feline?

00:06:02:120000.Dialogue: I'm trying to determine whether crying infants above my head are a possibility.

00:06:25:180000.Speaker: Alicia
00:06:25:180000.Dialogue: Thanks so much for helping me.

00:06:28:200000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:28:200000.Dialogue: Thank you so much for giving me the opportunity to help.

00:06:35:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:35:000000.Dialogue: This is Alicia, our new neighbor.

00:06:48:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:48:180000.Dialogue: She's still on probation, of course, but I like her.

00:06:53:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:53:100000.Dialogue: Oh, I don't usually dress like this. I'm going jogging.

00:07:00:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:00:130000.Dialogue: True, but the more likely explanation is that you're out of clean clothes again.

00:07:08:060000.Speaker: Alicia
00:07:08:060000.Dialogue: Please, you look cute. I'm dressed like a slob today, too.

00:07:20:150000.Speaker: Alicia
00:07:20:150000.Dialogue: Thanks for the warning. - I'll see you around.

00:07:27:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:07:27:230000.Dialogue: I'm dressed like a slob today, too.

00:07:32:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:32:010000.Dialogue: I enjoy mimicry. I've been working on Admiral Ackbar from Return of the Jedi.

00:07:42:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:42:050000.Dialogue: You have to imagine me with a giant squid head.

00:07:50:230000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:52:000000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.

00:08:26:020000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:26:020000.Dialogue: Come. Congratulations, I see you did your laundry.

00:08:32:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:32:140000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:08:34:140000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:34:140000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:37:110000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:37:110000.Speaker: Penny

00:08:40:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:40:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:40:100000.Dialogue: Oh. All right, that's cool, no biggie. He said he'd help me set up my printer, but I guess I can wait. What exactly is he doing up there?

00:08:47:230000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:47:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:08:47:230000.Dialogue: In what I can only perceive as a tactical move to destroy me, he is with Wolowitz and Koothrappali setting up her stereo.

00:08:55:100000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:55:100000.Speaker: Penny
00:08:55:100000.Dialogue: Oh, they're all up there? Typical.

00:08:59:160000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:08:59:160000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:09:02:130000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:09:02:130000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:02:130000.Dialogue: Up until recently, they did not know her, and had no encounters with her in a previous location. They never went upstairs to visit the former tenants. Your characterization of their behavior as typical is demonstrably fallacious.

00:09:16:170000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:09:16:170000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:16:170000.Dialogue: Now I see the giant squid head.

00:09:26:120000.Scene: The apartment. Sheldon is writing on an imaginary board. There is a knock on the door.
00:09:26:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:09:26:120000.Dialogue: Oh, great! Now, I have to start all over again.

00:09:31:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:31:130000.Dialogue: Yeah, I thought about renting this apartment, but I'm really more of a downtown loft kind of guy.

00:09:38:050000.Speaker: Alicia
00:09:38:050000.Dialogue: Cool. So are you in a loft now?

00:09:40:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:40:050000.Dialogue: Oh, actually, I'm, living with a woman in Altadena. Purely platonic. She's also my maid.

00:09:56:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:09:56:200000.Dialogue: I just wanted to bring you a little housewarming gift.

00:09:59:060000.Speaker: Alicia
00:09:59:060000.Dialogue: That is so sweet. - Come on in. Let's open it.

00:10:04:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:04:130000.Dialogue: This? I'm dressed like a slob today.

00:10:09:020000.Speaker: Alicia
00:10:09:020000.Dialogue: The guys have been helping me set up my sound system. I've never had such good-looking technical support.

00:10:19:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:19:040000.Dialogue: I don't know, it means shucks. Shucks means shucks. Let one go once in a while.

00:10:27:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:27:160000.Dialogue: You want to hear something awesome?

00:10:30:090000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:30:090000.Dialogue: Alicia is an actress, just like you.

00:10:36:190000.Speaker: Alicia
00:10:36:190000.Dialogue: Well, trying to be, but it's so hard.

00:10:38:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:38:210000.Dialogue: - I know, tell me about it.

00:10:48:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:10:48:110000.Dialogue: That's why I work at the Cheesecake Factory. I'm holding out for the right part.

00:10:56:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:56:220000.Dialogue: What do you want as your default setting for DVDs, 5.1 Dolby or DTS?

00:11:01:120000.Speaker: Alicia
00:11:01:120000.Dialogue: Whatever you think is best, cutie.

00:11:06:190000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:06:190000.Dialogue: Well, DTS has more low end, so...

00:11:14:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:14:230000.Dialogue: Hey, guys, guys, you will really appreciate this. I read the best science joke. You won't get it, but it's right up their alley.

00:11:22:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:22:060000.Dialogue: Anyway, this physicist goes into an ice cream parlor every week and orders an ice cream sundae for himself, and then offers one to the empty stool sitting next to him. This goes on for a while until the owner finally asks him what he's doing. The man says, Well, I'm a physicist, and quantum mechanics... teaches us

00:11:40:140000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:40:140000.Dialogue: that it is possible for the matter above this stool to spontaneously turn into a beautiful woman who might accept my offer and fall in love with me.

00:11:48:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:48:060000.Dialogue: The owner then says, Lots of single, beautiful women come in here ever day. Buy an ice cream for one of them, and they might fall in love with you. And the physicist says, Yeah, but what are the odds of that happening?

00:12:04:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:04:150000.Dialogue: It's a little insulting, don't you think?

00:12:07:090000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:07:090000.Dialogue: How would I know? I'm not even sure I get it.

00:12:11:230000.Speaker: Alicia
00:12:11:230000.Dialogue: Leonard? If you're done with the DVD player, can you set up my printer?

00:12:19:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:12:19:230000.Dialogue: Maybe when you're done with her printer, you could set up mine. You know, like you promised... a week ago.

00:12:25:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:12:25:000000.Dialogue: Yeah, I'll get to it. Don't nag me.

00:13:00:000000.Dialogue: - Well, they're all still up there.

00:13:06:100000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:06:100000.Dialogue: That's Wolowitz in his stacked heels that fool no one.

00:13:11:060000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:11:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:11:060000.Dialogue: I don't even know why I care. I don't care. Enough to memorize that stupid joke, but that's all I care.

00:13:19:050000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:19:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:13:19:050000.Dialogue: You know, Penny, there's something that occurs in beehives you might find interesting. Occasionally, a new queen will arrive while the old queen is still in power. When this happens, the old queen must either locate to a new hive or engage in a battle to the death until only one queen remains.

00:13:41:180000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:41:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:13:41:180000.Dialogue: What are you saying, that I'm threatened by Alicia? I'm like the old queen of the hive and it's just time for me to go?

00:13:48:110000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:48:110000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:51:150000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:51:150000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:54:220000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:54:220000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:13:59:000000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:13:59:000000.Speaker: Penny

00:14:04:030000.Scene: The apartment. Penny walks in without knocking and collapses on the sofa.
00:14:04:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:04:030000.Dialogue: I just got that physicist joke.

00:14:10:110000.Speaker: Leonard
00:14:10:110000.Dialogue: Gee, Penny, thanks for buying us dinner.

00:14:20:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:20:070000.Dialogue: Did you remember to ask for the chicken to be diced, not shredded? Even though the menu description specifies shredded? Brown rice, not white? Did you stop at the grocery for the good hot mustard? And pick up the low-sodium soy sauce from the market? Good.

00:14:39:010000.Speaker: Penny
00:14:39:010000.Dialogue: What do we got going on tonight? Playing Halo, watching Battlestar, drop some Mentos in Diet Coke?

00:14:59:090000.Speaker: Alicia
00:14:59:090000.Dialogue: - Thank God you're home. I need help.

00:15:01:230000.Speaker: Alicia
00:15:01:230000.Dialogue: I got a callback to audition for CSI to play a hooker who gets killed.

00:15:09:040000.Speaker: Alicia
00:15:09:040000.Dialogue: But my car is in the shop, and I have to be at Universal in 45 minutes.

00:15:16:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:16:080000.Dialogue: - I'll run lines with you in the car.

00:15:31:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:31:030000.Dialogue: They're gone, Penny. They can't hear you.

00:15:35:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:35:160000.Dialogue: I cannot believe they're letting her just use them like that. Anything she wants, they go panting after her like trained dogs. You know last week, she had Howard drive all the way to her uncle's house in Orange County to pick up her TV?

00:15:47:180000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:47:180000.Dialogue: You once had Leonard and me get your television from your ex-boyfriend.

00:15:56:210000.Speaker: Penny
00:15:56:210000.Dialogue: I'm telling you, that girl is a user, skating through life on her looks, taking advantage of weak-willed men, getting auditions for stupid network shows. It just creams my corn.

00:16:20:080000.Speaker: Alicia
00:16:20:080000.Dialogue: Guess what? I got the part on CSI.

00:16:28:080000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:28:080000.Dialogue: No, you know, congratulations. I think you'll make a great hooker.

00:16:33:130000.Speaker: Alicia
00:16:33:130000.Dialogue: Thank you. I got to ask you something.

00:16:43:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:43:040000.Dialogue: I don't know. I don't think a lot.

00:16:49:180000.Speaker: Alicia
00:16:49:180000.Dialogue: Well, got to run. The guys promised to set up my satellite dish and paint my bedroom.

00:16:57:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:16:57:060000.Dialogue: Can I talk to you about that for a second?

00:17:01:230000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:01:230000.Dialogue: You know, it's just that Leonard and Howard and Raj, they aren't like other guys. They're special.

00:17:12:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:12:130000.Dialogue: Let's see. How can I explain this? They don't know how to use their shields.

00:17:27:060000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:27:060000.Dialogue: Where the hell'd that come from?

00:17:30:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:30:190000.Dialogue: Anyways, you know how guys like this are, so... please don't take advantage of them.

00:17:38:230000.Speaker: Alicia
00:17:38:230000.Dialogue: Who says I'm taking advantage of them?

00:17:42:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:17:42:040000.Dialogue: Come on. They're doing everything for you, because you're leading them on.

00:17:46:050000.Speaker: Alicia
00:17:46:050000.Dialogue: So I let them do stuff for me. They're happy. I get stuff. Who cares? And how's it any different from what you do?

00:17:57:210000.Speaker: Alicia
00:17:57:210000.Dialogue: I've seen you around them. Are you pretending like you don't do the exact same thing?

00:18:02:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:18:02:180000.Dialogue: Okay, lady, you are way out of line.

00:18:12:040000.Speaker: Alicia
00:18:12:040000.Dialogue: What are you going to do about it, bitch?

00:18:18:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:18:160000.Dialogue: I like Green Lantern. I'm just saying it's pretty lame that he can be defeated by the color yellow.

00:18:24:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:18:24:150000.Dialogue: Only the modern Green Lantern is vulnerable to yellow.

00:18:27:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:18:27:230000.Dialogue: Golden age Green Lantern was vulnerable to wood.

00:18:30:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:18:30:210000.Dialogue: Great, so I can take them both out with a number-two pencil?

00:18:56:080000.Dialogue: May I say you look very comely tonight?
